The '''forest white-eye''' or '''Cameroon green white-eye''' ('''''Zosterops stenocricotus''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Zosteropidae]]. It is found from southeastern [[Nigeria]] to southwestern [[Central African Republic]] and northern [[Gabon]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://avibase.bsc-eoc.org/species.jsp?avibaseid=284585666827A6C8|title=Zosterops stenocricotus (Forest White-eye) - Avibase|website=avibase.bsc-eoc.org|accessdate=4 April 2023}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ebird.org/species/afywhe1|title=Forest White-eye - eBird|website=ebird.org|accessdate=4 April 2023}}</ref>

Its natural [[habitat]]s are subtropical, tropical moist [[montane forest]]s, and subtropical or tropical high-altitude [[shrubland]]. It is threatened by [[habitat loss]].

